review_text:
{"en": "Nice location with brilliant spa service.

However rated a 4 as there was power outage and it took almost 7 mins before light was restored.

Found that strange given its a five star hotel. Light should come on in a flash!"}

{"en": "Radisson Blu is a premium hotel located in Ikeja, offering a blend of comfort, elegance, and modern luxury. The hotel features beautifully designed rooms that are spacious, well-furnished, and thoughtfully arranged to ensure a relaxing stay. The views from the rooms are lovely and add to the overall calming atmosphere of the hotel.
One of the highlights of my visit was the buffet. It was well presented, visually appealing, and offered a wide variety of delicious options, making the dining experience both satisfying and enjoyable. The ambience of the dining area was warm and inviting, adding to the experience.

Overall, I had a really nice time at Radisson Blu. The environment, comfort, and quality service made my visit memorable, and it’s definitely a place I would recommend for both leisure and business stays."}

{"en": "My stay at Radisson Blu was excellent and very comfortable. The hotel has a classy, modern atmosphere and the rooms were spotless, spacious, and well-designed. The bed was especially comfortable, making it easy to relax after a long day.

The staff were professional, friendly, and always willing to help, which really enhanced the experience. The location is convenient, and the facilities from the restaurant to the general ambience are top-notch.

The only minor reason it’s not a perfect 5 is that a few services could be slightly faster during peak hours. Overall, Radisson Blu delivers quality, comfort, and great value. I would definitely recommend it and look forward to staying again"}

{"en": "My stay at Radisson blu hotel exceeded my expectations in every way. From the moment I arrived, the front‑desk team was warm, efficient, and eager to help. My room was spacious, immaculate, and offered a comfortable night’s sleep, with high‑quality linens and a well‑stocked bathroom.

The location was ideal—close enough to attractions and dining options, yet quiet enough to unwind after a day out. The on‑site restaurant served a variety of tasty dishes, and the breakfast spread was fresh and satisfying. Amenities like the rooftop pool and spa added a nice touch.

Overall, the service, cleanliness, and facilities made for a memorable stay. I’d definitely return and recommend it to anyone looking for a reliable, comfortable place to stay."}

{"en": "I booked one of the halls for my little event on Thursday 12th of June, it was a very terrible and bad experience. We paid for buffet food for 60 guests, the food we got was not enough for 20 guests ordinarily talk more of buffet. It was really bad. A guy called Wilson was in charge and we kept pleading with him to help sort things out as majority of our guests hadn’t eaten. He kept insisting we had to pay more. A buffet is meant to be served in surplus but this is the worse I have ever seen in my life, it was way too short. We the host had nothing to eat as our majority of our guests ddnt see food to eat.

Wilson was so rude and wasn’t reasonable. The head of that department and that entire team cheated us so much and I regret ever booking this place.

Please don’t book your events at Radisson blu if you don’t want to be dissappointed."}

{"en": "Had a very nice time out with friends at the dinner buffet.

Great meals and wide varieties too.

Recommended."}

{"en": "This hotel is a really nice hotel. Their services are very close to excellent.

The ambience is breath-taking: Guests are welcomed by a team of professional receptionist and soft music which synchronises one's state with the calm and peaceful environment.

One would almost be tempted to speak only with whispers, so as not to disrupt the peace and quiet."}

{"en": "Came in for fine dining. I was completely wowed by the ambience, the decor, the atmosphere. It was breathtaking.

But then I take my order and it takes more than 40 minutes to get my meal. Cocktails take another 10 minutes. The wait almost ruin the experience.

Thankfully I had good conversations, the low calming music helped."}

{"en": "This building is really attractive and has good environment. There is an adequate parking space too.

Although, when I used their facility I didn't go for a hotel accommodation but the hall during a programme.

They have both make and female as their staff and the staff were really courteous and attended to clients appropriately."}

{"en": "We had an event in one of halls ( ijakadji )  last weekend , the staff were so helpful , from Zanab , to Wilson , mr Simeon , Peter … the food was very good .. The ac worked very well, we had to be them to reduce at some point .

The was a lot of portions to choose from

In all , it was amazing ! Thank you to Zanab , she did all the reservations with no itch …"}

{"en": "This hotel is really great and is very modern in its design approach. The rooms are spacious and as I mentioned it's decor is really nice. The rooms are clean and all amenities are provided

Amani Spa is heavenly, the staff are friendly and genuine. I had a full body massage and it was incredible. I would definitely go back

The hotel staff arranged a cake for me as it was my birthday and along with that they sang for me so overall a great stay and I highly recommend it"}

{"en": "Great hotel. Rather expensive. My host was a guest which allowed me access to the lounge.

The lounge itself is quiet and spacious. Ideal if you work remotely. It's also a self serve arrangement.

The hotel overall is tastefully furnished."}

{"en": "Very Nice rooms , great breakfast spread (the mushroom and onions are to die for) unfortunately, rooms on the the third floor are NOT sound-proof so you can hear every sound coming from the poolside bar (not very restful).

A bit weird that most of the TV channels available were in Arabic though....

Excellent service from the staff and pretty bathroom."}

{"en": "When I wanted to give my best friend a treat for her birthday, I decided to check the reviews on Renaissance and I was impressed so I decided to take a leap.

We were sooooo blown away, amazing service, top notch interior decor and the food was as tasty. Everything about it was perfect and we had such a great time. The staff were polite and it had the right ambience about it. I cannot wait to return.
Thank you."}

{"en": "Nice edifice with exceptional services ranging from accommodation, halls for events and conferences, nice restaurant and bar.

Staff are professional and courteous most of them were with a smile on. The facilities team were supportive and we had a smooth run of our event.

#meetTheGinger"}

{"en": "I love the aura that Radisson Blu brings. The ambience is just amazing and the seating is comfortable.

One time I was really cold and I asked for tea to help and the waiter also came with natural ginger because it would help me get better faster. That was really thoughtful.

Often times, I hold meetings here because I love the service."}

{"en": "The server Blessing and Feyisola are so wonderful
They actually made my day as I was given a wow experience …. With their service am sure I would b coming here steadily…

They made me enjoyed my birthday celebration and am so delighted"}

{"en": "Checked in to celebrate a landmark birthday for my wife. The room was comfortable and beautiful. The central Air-conditioning system was super effective as the room was pre-cooled beyond comfort; the control had to be switched off to get the right temperature back!

Unfortunately, quite unexpectedly, all the lights suddenly went off along with the hotel WiFi followed by the intercom system. No communication was possible and confusion set in. Was it sabotage or just breakdown of power supply? The situation subsisted for upwards of an hour!

Till we checked out, no apologies were made nor explanations given for the power failure! Albeit, I scored them 4 stars since I do not expect it to be a regular event!"}

{"en": "I enjoyed Radisson Blu hotel. The staff were very friendly and gave me tips on how to make my room warmer. My sheets were always changed on time, the bed was soft and comfortable. The TV had a couple of music stations which was a plus to me as it seems like quite a number of hotels usually forget to include music channels in their Channel subscriptions/bouquet.

I however wasn't entitled to a complimentary breakfast which was strange as my booking stated that I was entitled to this service, but the hotel said otherwise.

I enjoyed my stay nonetheless; as I ran into an old friend whilst at the hotel and I liked the view from my room, especially at night when the hotel’s blue lights would shine from atop the building."}

{"en": "Beautiful environment. The lounge is perfect for meetings and chills. It has a snacks/tea area for meetings, discourse, etc. The bar area-which is close to the snooker board allows for light meals like burger, chicken wings, etc. Speaking of the burger, I’ve had their beef burger twice on separate occasions & noticed that both were salty. You may want to advice the chef if looking to have this.

You can only eat proper meals at the restaurant upstairs. I think the breakfast buffet should be around 11k but funny enough it’s cheaper at their V.I branch; for 8k something. I’m still day dreaming about the cake I ate at the breakfast buffet at their V.I branch. & of cos, the bacon was salty (why must one thing be salty chef Radisson?)

In all, I really loved the place & would keep visiting."}

owner_responses:
{"en": {"text": "Thank you Sagir, for sharing your comments during your stay with us.  We rely on guest feedback to determine both the positive and negative aspects of our hotel and to improve wherever possible. Your interest and concern are therefore extremely valuable to us, and we hope that you will be staying with us again soon. We should welcome another opportunity to show you Radisson Blu Hotel Lagos Ikeja’s Hospitality at its best!

Regards

Jeffrey"}}

review_text:
{"en": "I had a chance to visit the hotel and I must say, interior décor/design is absolutely on point. It is obvious that attention has been paid to the details. First thing I noticed was certain security measures put in place. You can definitely sense the difference from many other hotels in the country with how much effort has been put into this development.

Atmosphere is a mixture of modernism with an African twist. Quality of furnishing is very impressive, there was a set of doors where raw wood (that seemed like they were just cut from trees and processed) was used without any refinement to them. I really like the transitions the floors go through (with reference to look|feel|texture) as you move from one area to another. Conference rooms are definitely to be considered for your next set of meetings. I like the use of the water fountains on the outside, as they give a calming effect to the hotel environment, thus making you feel you're in a different part of the world and not in Ikeja/Lagos.

Definitely a contender for hotel lodging in Lagos. Looking forward to service delivery and food reviews."}

{"en": "Radisson Hotel Ikeja, Lagos delivers an outstanding hospitality experience on every level. The rooms are top-tier—spacious, modern, and impeccably maintained, offering both comfort and style that make your stay truly relaxing.

The service is excellent, with staff who are professional, courteous, and always ready to help, ensuring you feel well taken care of from check-in to check-out. The buffet and restaurant services are equally impressive, offering a wide variety of well-prepared dishes served in a refined and welcoming setting. Everything is fresh, flavorful, and presented to a high standard.

Overall, Radisson Hotel Ikeja stands out for its quality, consistency, and attention to detail. Whether for business or leisure, it’s a top choice in Lagos and a place you’ll be happy to return to."}

{"en": "A luxurious hotel with great ambience right from the entrance. You feel the atmosphere of elegance, and royalty once you step in.

The menu at the restaurant is awesome. Great place for business meetings and family lunch/dinner as well.

Parking is at the basement."}

{"en": "Pros: Excellent room size as compared to many other hotels in same category.
Location is safe with good restaurants around.

Cons: the service is slow and a bit inattentive"}

{"en": "Really nice spot, had a quiet hangout with my girlfriend, the food was good. We ordered goatmeat pepper soup  and club sandwich. Soft drinks are sold from N900 while mocktails go from N2000.

We sat by the pool side, it had a beautiful view. The only downside was there were flies especially when our meals came in. The waitress didn't do anything to control the flies. For a place like that, you'll expect better control of this.

Overall service was good and we had a good time, i'll visit again."}

{"en": "Good organisation at the car park, good security measures and an average customer service (experience) 🙂.

I really think the available car park is not sufficient during the peak period and they need to do some magic here 🙂. The Mgt seem to have put some sort of palliative in place - staff to organise things during such peak period.

Succinctly stated, great experience!👍🏽"}

{"en": "It's always a beautiful and relaxing experience at Radisson Blu Hotel.

I typically go to the bar area on Sundays and I'm impressed with how courteous the staff conduct themselves.

Drinks are from N900 upwards and I find the complimentary nuts tasting. 🙂"}

{"en": "Went for the Sunday brunch. Starts at 12 noon. 13k per adult. Includes water and one complimentary glass of chapman. There's a wide enough spread. Intercontinental. But there wasn't even yam. I wanted to try their egg sauce but wasn't yam. I really liked the turkey stew. And the cowleg was good, had ugba in it. There were prawns, lamb, chicken, turkey,fish, peppersoup,etc. They had different sorts of bread/pastries. It's family friendly too.

Good aesthetics/lighting for pictures.

Bathroom was clean and dry.."}

{"en": "Steak house and good burger !!!! If you find yourself idle on Thursday or Friday evening , you may just need a drive down to Isaac John and find Radisson Blu. Very good for private events also in an almost sound proof event room . I have not slept in the hotel yet but i was in one of the rooms once , you will love it 😎👍.

Ah! The Salmon is also nice and fresh !

Close your day with a cup of coffee ? , they brew it good also."}

{"en": "Radisson Blu Hotel Ikeja has a top notch service from the entrance to the halls and room service. I believe they are in top 10 of the best hotels in the country.

Their food was good with a lot of variety to choose from.

Good ambience had an easy access location."}

{"en": "It is a nice hotel with good food. Very clean.

Great location, as it is close to the airport.

As for the staff attitude, needs massive improvement. Both at the reception and Restaurant."}

{"en": "The Hotel offers top notch service, good food, large halls and good spots to take photographs.

It seems to be the rendezvous for the Rich and highly influential figures in Nigeria .
I ran into two past Governors, Musicians and a Nollywood star."}

owner_responses:
{"en": {"text": "Benjamin,
Thank you for your response, do come back again.

A.M"}}

review_text:
{"en": "I was at Cut Steakhouse for lunch and had chicken breast and mashed potatoes.

I liked the calmness in the restaurant and the courteous staff.

It's on the ground floor of the hotel."}

{"en": "Truly worth a 5star! Radisson Blu Hotel Isaac John, GRA, Ikeja's Customer service excellent! ☀️👌

Their sales director, Ada, deserves an award! Her customer service is out if this world! Another staff, Atobatele, ensured our wait time to check in was not long.

The special treatment I and my parents got from her when lodged there beat our imagination! Kudos to Ada, Atobatele and team."}
